   // Slightly easier keybindings for navigating search results:
   // - ctrl+g instead of cmd+shift+g for find previous (this is easier, and note the
   //   mnemonic that, on my Kinesis keyboard, ctrl is above cmd - hence ctrl for finding
   //   up and cmd for finding down).
   // - Add shift to cmd+g or ctrl+g to find next/previous selection (mnemonic: shift
   //   selects things)
   // - Down and up arrows instead of enter / shift-enter for navigating find results.
   //   Note that this overrides using the arrows for navigating history, but opt+up /
   //   opt+down can already be used for that, too.
   {
      "key": "ctrl+g",
      "command": "editor.action.previousMatchFindAction",
      "when": "editorFocus"
